@exceptionfactory From my admittedly limited reading the impression I had is that these native implementations become substantially more efficient at high rates/high scale/many concurrent connections/etc..  I suspect we'd not see it in routine testing but rather in deliberately pushing the agenda.  

With that in mind I am more inclined to suggest this only be activated via a profile allowing evaluation over time but avoiding inclusion in the normal case for now.  

Just my two cents.  I'm cool with a different approach too.

@greyp9 I ran through some integration and runtime tests, evaluating the configuration experience in particular. I adjusted the property ordering in the Processors and Controller Service to follow a logical group of required and then optional, and also keeping groups of dependent properties together.

I made one substantive change to the Transaction Isolation Level property, changing it to a described value instead of a Boolean, which is what I had intended in a previous comment. This way, it reflects the Kafka property value directly, and has corresponding description information.

With these changes, I am planning to merge pending successful automated builds.

@exceptionfactory Thanks for merging. Two points.

1. I noticed that the `poi-utils` module is really not necessary. The one enum which it has `ProtectionType` was only moved to this new module if the `SplitExcel` and `ExcelReader` were going to be in two different modules so that both could utilize this for password protected Excel files. Now that they are all under one module `nifi-poi-services`, `ProtectionType` can be moved back there although still remain in its own file.
2. If I would like this change in the 1.x, I assume I have to make a separate PR, right?

@EndzeitBegins It is effectively a non starter to merge new things into the 2.x/main line that are intentionally restrained to also go back into the 1.x line.  We moved on for a lot of good reasons and the entire point is to leverage the language benefits of Java 21 and newer.

As-is given the above this PR should not proceed.

To be clear I'm not commenting on the idea itself - hopefully others can review/engage on that but the PR for this capability should target the 2.x line and benefits that come with that.  I don't recommend backporting at all but that is not a hard rule.
